		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yet Mode 7 in games like F-Zero didn't have the same effect on public perception of the 65C816.</div>
<br />Maybe because Mode 7 was used in marketing, so that it was understood that it was a feature of the video processor. I recall having seen the term "mode 7" in one or more of those brochures they sent out to Nintendo Club members here in Sweden in the early '90s (and those were usually very low on technical details).

		

		</td>
